President Donald Trump has issued a statement declaring a national emergency with regards to the actions and policies of certain members of the Government of Belarus. This national emergency was initially declared in 2006 and is being extended for another year. The actions and policies of these individuals pose a threat to the national security and foreign policy of the United States. The specific concerns include undermining Belarus's democratic processes, committing human rights abuses, and engaging in public corruption. The extension of this national emergency will continue to address these issues. The statement was published in the Federal Register and transmitted to Congress.